channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Trump Legal Team Asks for Sentencing Delay in New York Case
'Pregnant persons': Ohio Sen Sherrod Brown scrubbed 'women' from bill on pregnancy
item.description: Sen. Brown erased women from his most recent version of a bill relating to health insurance enrollment periods for pregnant women.

item.title: Karl Rove: Trump Needs 'Reset' to Hone Attacks on Harris
item.description: Republican political strategist Karl Rove said time is running short for Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump to prosecute "precise lines of attack" on Kamala Harris — namely her policy "flip-flops" — while offering up new policy ideas that can win swing states.

item.title: I'm Sorry, What? Secret Service Agent Abandoned Post at Trump NC Event to Breastfeed
'Election interference': Trump lawyers call for delayed sentencing in Bragg case
item.description: Lawyers for former President Trump are requesting his sentencing hearing in New York v. Trump be postponed until after the November presidential election.

item.title: Rep. Bergman to Newsmax: Walz Has 'Reputation as a Liar'
item.description: Rep. Jack Bergman, R-Mich., told Newsmax on Thursday that Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz "would be best served" if he stepped aside as Vice President Kamala Harris' running mate over allegations of stolen valor.

item.title: Harris Campaign Throws Streamer Under the Bus After He Declines to Collab With Her, but He Strikes Back
Harris does about-face on several far-left policies, distances herself from Biden
item.description: Kamala Harris flip-flopped on at least five liberal policy stances on mandatory assault rifle buybacks, fracking, immigration, health care and job guarantees.

item.title: Montana Poll: GOP's Sheehy Up 6 Points in Senate Race
item.description: Republican candidate Tim Sheehy holds a 6-point lead over incumbent Democrat Sen. Jon Tester in the race for a U.S. Senate seat in Montana, according to a new poll.

item.title: OPINION: Biden May Not Have Betrayed Mossad Agents to Iran but the Proof It Didn't Happen Is Lacking
RFK Jr. asked Harris for Cabinet post in exchange for dropping out, endorsing her: report
item.description: Independent presidential candidate Robert F. Kennedy Jr. attempted to meet with Vice President Kamala Harris to discuss the possibility of serving in her administration.

item.title: Gold Star Dad to Newsmax: Taliban Parade 'Disgusting'
item.description: Gold Star father Darin Hoover experienced "anger all over again" watching the Taliban parade around in billions' worth of U.S. military equipment, calling it a "disgusting" display nearly three years after his son and 12 other American service members were killed in Afghanistan.

item.title: Protesters Infiltrated NYC Dem Rally for Harris, Then Came Cops, Smoke Bombs, and Some Funny Notes
Harris camp silent on when VP will hold press conference as Trump preps to host his second in a week
item.description: The Harris campaign has not revealed when Vice President Kamala Harris plans to hold a formal press conference since she emerged as the Democratic nominee weeks ago.

item.title: Gen. Wesley Clark to Newsmax: Afghanistan War a 'Tragedy'
item.description: The war in Afghanistan was a failure, retired Army Gen. Wesley Clark told Newsmax Thursday.
